; Record format (read by #R$84ED/#R$7E4F with the sprite number in L):
; record[0..1] = sprite data address (LE word); record[2] = height in 8px rows,
; top bit masked off before use ($7F) -- meaning of that bit not yet confirmed,
; may just be unused/reserved; record[3] = width in 8px columns, but bit 7 here
; is a live flip-flop flag: #R$7E4F XORs it in place (self-modifying table
; entry) on every call, toggling it between the two calls needed to draw a
; sprite's normal and mirrored/second-buffer image, then masks it off ($7F) to
; get the actual width.
